paragraphs.title: Read Data from CSV
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.sql._

val CSVNames = Array("parcours.csv","customers.csv","products.csv","visitors.csv") 
val data = new Array[DataFrame](CSVNames.length)
val pathToFiles = "file:///Users/jux/Desktop/TPT/tpt_commerce_dataset_exemple_01_corrige/"
for(i <- 0 to CSVNames.length-1)
{
    var dataCSV = spark.read
        .option("inferSchema", "true")
        .option("header", "true")
        .option("mode", "DROPMALFORMED")
        .csv(pathToFiles+CSVNames(i))
        .cache()
    val nameDF = CSVNames(i).split('.')
    dataCSV.createOrReplaceTempView(nameDF(0))
    dataCSV.printSchema()
    data(i) = dataCSV
}

//"parcours.csv","customers.csv","products.csv","visitors.csv
val parcours = data(0)  // parcours des clients et des visiteurs sur les produits
val customers = data(1)   // info sur les clients avec un compte
val products = data(2)   // infos sur les produits
val visitors = data(3)   // infos sur les visiteurs

paragraphs.title: Top 10 products -> recommendations for totally new user
paragraphs.text:
// get the most viewed item for hot-items recommandations
val top_10_most_viewed_items = spark.sql(
    "SELECT product_id, count(*) as numberOfViewsForItem " +
    "FROM parcours " +
    "GROUP BY product_id " +
    "ORDER BY numberOfViewsForItem DESC " +
    "LIMIT 10")
top_10_most_viewed_items.createOrReplaceTempView("top_10_most_viewed_items")
top_10_most_viewed_items.printSchema()
top_10_most_viewed_items.show(10,false)

paragraphs.title: Top 10 categories -> recommendation for totally new user
paragraphs.text:
// get the most viewed categories for hot-categories recommandations
val top_10_most_viewed_categories = spark.sql(
    "SELECT category_id, count(*) as numberOfViewsForCategorie " +
    "FROM parcours, products " +
    "WHERE parcours.product_id = products.product_id AND category_id is not null " +
    "GROUP BY category_id " +
    "ORDER BY numberOfViewsForCategorie DESC " +
    "LIMIT 10")
top_10_most_viewed_categories.createOrReplaceTempView("top_10_most_viewed_categories")
top_10_most_viewed_categories.printSchema()
top_10_most_viewed_categories.show(10,false)

paragraphs.title: Visiteurs les plus actifs
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT visitor_id, count(*) as nb_vues
FROM parcours
WHERE visitor_id is not null
GROUP BY visitor_id
ORDER BY nb_vues DESC
LIMIT 10

paragraphs.title: Clients les plus actifs
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT customer_id, count(*) as nb_vues
FROM parcours
WHERE customer_id is not null
GROUP BY customer_id
ORDER BY nb_vues DESC
LIMIT 10

paragraphs.title: Timestamp des consultations par client
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT customer_id, count(*) as nb_vues, collect_list(distinct(timestamp))
FROM parcours
WHERE customer_id is not null
GROUP BY customer_id
ORDER BY nb_vues DESC
LIMIT 50

paragraphs.title: Parcours d'un client -> TS +  10 produits + catégorie produit + infos client
paragraphs.text:
var customerHistory = parcours.select("*").where("customer_id='5ae99132ecb5983cbef24c7966d4dcc2e4189db8'")
                                          .join(products, products("product_id")===parcours("product_id"))
                                          .toDF("visitor_id","customer_id","produit_product_id", "timestamp", "parcours_product_id", "category_id")
                                          .filter(products("category_id").isNotNull)
                                          .orderBy("timestamp")
                                          .limit(10)
                                          
customerHistory = customerHistory.groupBy("customer_id").agg(collect_list("parcours_product_id").as("listes_produits"),collect_list("category_id").as("categorie_produits"))

customerHistory.printSchema()
customerHistory = customerHistory.select(col("customer_id"), expr("listes_produits[0]"), expr("listes_produits[1]"), expr("listes_produits[2]"), expr("listes_produits[3]"), expr("listes_produits[4]"), expr("listes_produits[5]"),  expr("categorie_produits[0]"), expr("categorie_produits[1]"), expr("categorie_produits[2]"), expr("categorie_produits[3]"), expr("categorie_produits[4]"), expr("categorie_produits[5]"))

customerHistory.show(false)
customerHistory.createOrReplaceTempView("customerHistory")
